00:40:38,740 --> 00:40:41,613
and he enables her to
do it and makes their
10-year-old help.

795
00:40:41,656 --> 00:40:43,266
That's wonderful?

796
00:40:43,310 --> 00:40:45,617
You make them sound awful.

797
00:40:45,660 --> 00:40:48,402
You came to me because
you were worried
about the children.

798
00:40:48,446 --> 00:40:50,752
And child abuse is
what I investigate.

799
00:40:50,796 --> 00:40:52,188
Because it's a crime.

800
00:40:54,016 --> 00:40:56,976
You are completely
twisting my words.

801
00:40:57,019 --> 00:40:58,586
I'm sorry I came.

802
00:40:58,630 --> 00:41:00,980
I'm just repeating the story
that you told me, that's all.

803
00:41:03,199 --> 00:41:04,462
May I have those
notes please?

804
00:41:04,940 --> 00:41:07,203
No.

805
00:41:07,247 --> 00:41:09,467
Are you sure you're just not
afraid of losing your job?

806
00:41:10,642 --> 00:41:11,947
You do have a green card.

807
00:41:28,050 --> 00:41:29,487
[SNIFFS] Mmm.

808
00:41:29,530 --> 00:41:30,531
Smell those, Maggie.

809
00:41:30,575 --> 00:41:32,011
Mmm. Are those good?

810
00:41:32,054 --> 00:41:34,883
And look, raspberries,
your favorite.

811
00:41:34,927 --> 00:41:36,015
I'll take these.

812
00:41:42,195 --> 00:41:43,326
ANNIE: Sam?

813
00:41:43,370 --> 00:41:44,502
Sam?

814
00:41:45,198 --> 00:41:46,242
Sam!

815
00:41:54,599 --> 00:41:56,818
Hey. I missed you.

816
00:41:58,385 --> 00:41:59,429
Mom.

817
00:41:59,473 --> 00:42:01,519
What, baby?

818
00:42:01,562 --> 00:42:04,826
Are there other
people like Maggie
that I can't see?

819
00:42:12,094 --> 00:42:13,182
I don't know.

820
00:42:14,444 --> 00:42:15,707
I can't hear them.

821
00:42:22,627 --> 00:42:23,976
Let's go home, baby.

822
00:42:25,891 --> 00:42:27,675
I asked Maggie.

823
00:42:27,719 --> 00:42:29,895
She said she doesn't know.

824
00:42:34,856 --> 00:42:36,597
Let's all go home. Okay?

825
00:42:47,216 --> 00:42:49,436
Oh, I'm sorry, honey.
I was off somewhere.

826
00:42:51,264 --> 00:42:53,135
No, you're not very sick.

827
00:42:53,179 --> 00:42:54,876
It's just a little fever.

828
00:43:02,057 --> 00:43:03,581
[INHALES]

829
00:43:03,624 --> 00:43:06,758
I guess Mommy's frightened.

830
00:43:06,801 --> 00:43:10,283
You know, mommies and
daddies get frightened
too sometimes.

831
00:43:12,851 --> 00:43:14,679
No. Not of the bogeyman.

832
00:43:19,074 --> 00:43:20,598
Let's say our prayers.

833
00:43:24,036 --> 00:43:26,778
Now I lay me down to sleep.

834
00:43:26,821 --> 00:43:28,954
I pray the Lord
my soul to keep.

835
00:43:30,042 --> 00:43:33,436
If I should die before I wake,

836
00:43:33,480 --> 00:43:35,395
I pray the Lord
my soul to take.

837
00:43:41,880 --> 00:43:44,360
Sweet dreams, honey.

838
00:43:44,404 --> 00:43:46,145
I know. I'll come back
to check on you.

839
00:43:50,236 --> 00:43:52,238
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

840
00:44:04,903 --> 00:44:06,948
TIM: Come on in.

841
00:44:06,992 --> 00:44:08,733
There's room for
a circus in here.

842
00:44:08,776 --> 00:44:10,343
I don't want
to disturb you.

843
00:44:10,386 --> 00:44:11,344
No, it's okay.

844
00:44:34,019 --> 00:44:35,063
[SIGHS]

845
00:44:37,544 --> 00:44:39,764
I guess Maggie
has a fever.

846
00:44:39,807 --> 00:44:41,026
I guess she does.

847
00:44:45,465 --> 00:44:47,728
I've never seen you
out here at night.

848
00:44:47,772 --> 00:44:48,990
Does that mean you're
out here every night?

849
00:44:49,904 --> 00:44:51,123
Is that all right?

850
00:44:51,166 --> 00:44:52,515
Sure. What's it for?

851
00:44:54,866 --> 00:44:57,433
It's my secret luxury.

852
00:44:57,477 --> 00:45:00,567
To sit in warm, bubbly
water under the stars

853
00:45:00,610 --> 00:45:03,048
and look at the silhouette
of the mountains

854
00:45:03,091 --> 00:45:05,746
and listen to the birds.

855
00:45:05,790 --> 00:45:07,095
Pretty far from England.

856
00:45:08,270 --> 00:45:11,230
I must sound really silly.

857
00:45:11,273 --> 00:45:14,450
Never be embarrassed of
being delighted, Gillian.

858
00:45:14,494 --> 00:45:15,843
That's something
Annie taught me.

859
00:45:19,194 --> 00:45:20,587
She seems sad tonight.

860
00:45:21,980 --> 00:45:23,546
I've never seen her like that.

861
00:45:23,590 --> 00:45:25,070
She's worried.

862
00:45:25,113 --> 00:45:26,898
She put the baby monitor
in Maggie's room.

863
00:45:29,770 --> 00:45:31,119
Could I...

864
00:45:31,163 --> 00:45:32,512
Ask me how it started?

865
00:45:33,731 --> 00:45:34,862
I'm sorry.

866
00:45:34,906 --> 00:45:36,559
I wondered when you would.

867
00:45:36,603 --> 00:45:38,953
No, I should let you
enjoy this in peace.

868
00:45:38,997 --> 00:45:41,086
You're very good
at all this.

869
00:45:41,129 --> 00:45:43,436
I'm sort of amazed.

870
00:45:43,479 --> 00:45:46,091
Sometimes I just
want to cry for Annie.

871
00:45:46,134 --> 00:45:48,746
Then I think of what
you must feel. And Doc.

872
00:45:51,531 --> 00:45:53,359
You want to know why she
does it? How it started?

873
00:45:55,796 --> 00:45:56,710
That's fair.

874
00:45:58,277 --> 00:45:59,931
You're kind of family by now.

875
00:46:02,542 --> 00:46:03,848
Are you hungry at all?

876
00:46:04,674 --> 00:46:05,632
Sure.

877
00:46:08,287 --> 00:46:10,202
It was, uh, five years ago.

878
00:46:11,507 --> 00:46:14,380
One morning I was
sitting here, having coffee

879
00:46:14,423 --> 00:46:16,817
like I do every morning.

880
00:46:16,861 --> 00:46:19,820
Annie comes into the
kitchen and she goes
to the stove and...

881
00:46:19,864 --> 00:46:21,126
She had her back to me.

882
00:46:22,344 --> 00:46:23,781
But when she turned,

883
00:46:23,824 --> 00:46:26,653
I could see she was
sterilizing baby bottles.

884
00:46:26,696 --> 00:46:29,612
And, and she was holding
something in her arms
something I couldn't see.

885
00:46:31,571 --> 00:46:32,790
She said,

886
00:46:34,356 --> 00:46:36,968
Maggie had kept her up
all night with colic.

887
00:46:39,666 --> 00:46:42,190
It seemed we had a new baby
whose name was Maggie.

888
00:46:43,278 --> 00:46:44,976
I thought it was a joke.

889
00:46:46,455 --> 00:46:49,241
Then Doc came in
and Annie asked her

890
00:46:49,284 --> 00:46:52,374
if Maggie had kept her
awake with her crying.

891
00:46:54,855 --> 00:46:56,378
My heart stopped.

892
00:46:58,119 --> 00:47:00,339
I didn't know what to do.

893
00:47:00,382 --> 00:47:02,471
Did you take her
to see someone?

894
00:47:02,515 --> 00:47:03,777
Psychiatrist? Sure.

895
00:47:05,605 --> 00:47:08,608
We went to one
of the best in town.

896
00:47:08,651 --> 00:47:10,262
We get to the door
of his office

897
00:47:10,305 --> 00:47:12,220
and Annie looks at me
with tears in her eyes
and says,

898
00:47:14,179 --> 00:47:16,007
"Please don't make
me go in there.

899
00:47:16,050 --> 00:47:17,443
"He'll take away my baby."

900
00:47:19,619 --> 00:47:21,360
Well, I had a pretty good
idea what he'd say

901
00:47:21,403 --> 00:47:24,189
so I went in alone
and listened.

902
00:47:24,232 --> 00:47:26,495
I got as many professional
opinions as I could.

903
00:47:28,671 --> 00:47:30,848
I learned that she
would almost certainly
be institutionalized.

904
00:47:33,894 --> 00:47:35,417
I couldn't do it.

905
00:47:36,984 --> 00:47:37,985
I couldn't do it.

906
00:47:41,946 --> 00:47:43,861
Did you say you
were hungry?

907
00:47:43,904 --> 00:47:45,645
Starving.Good. Me, too.

908
00:47:49,562 --> 00:47:53,348
I knew this had
to be something so
deep and desperate

909
00:47:53,392 --> 00:47:57,396
and I thought what terrible
damage it might do to her
to just rip it away.

910
00:47:59,572 --> 00:48:02,357
She wouldn't do this without
some extraordinary need.

911
00:48:03,358 --> 00:48:05,012
Did you talk to her about it?

912
00:48:06,622 --> 00:48:08,189
If it was something she
could have talked about

913
00:48:08,233 --> 00:48:09,277
I don't think it
would have happened.

914
00:48:13,978 --> 00:48:16,894
You know, for a long time, we,
we lived just for each other.

915
00:48:18,634 --> 00:48:20,636
My career was just taking off

916
00:48:20,680 --> 00:48:22,421
and if I had a gig
in Paris, we'd go.

917
00:48:24,292 --> 00:48:26,904
Or a weekend seminar in
Stockholm, we'd just go.

918
00:48:29,515 --> 00:48:30,777
We loved our life.

919
00:48:32,648 --> 00:48:34,302
I'd come home in the
middle of the day...

920
00:48:37,479 --> 00:48:42,006
Then Doc came along, and life
began to revolve around her.

921
00:48:42,049 --> 00:48:43,485
Annie loved being a mother.

922
00:48:43,529 --> 00:48:46,140
Ooh... She was in heaven.

923
00:48:48,577 --> 00:48:50,536
I was spending more
and more time at work.

924
00:48:52,103 --> 00:48:53,887
I was hot all of
a sudden and...

925
00:48:53,931 --> 00:48:56,716
You know, when that happens,
you just want to go with it.

926
00:48:56,759 --> 00:48:58,326
So, I was gone
a lot of the time.

927
00:49:01,068 --> 00:49:03,288
I think Annie blamed
herself for the change.

928
00:49:04,767 --> 00:49:06,508
She figured she'd
messed up somehow

929
00:49:06,552 --> 00:49:10,208
that her, her attention to Doc
was somehow driving us apart.

930
00:49:13,211 --> 00:49:15,039
So, she did the only
thing she could do.

931
00:49:16,562 --> 00:49:19,565
Do it again, only,
do it right this time.

932
00:49:22,133 --> 00:49:23,786
[SIGHS] Maggie.

933
00:49:26,180 --> 00:49:28,530
[SIGHS] Maggie.

934
00:49:33,187 --> 00:49:34,623
The funny thing is,

935
00:49:36,060 --> 00:49:37,800
Maggie did make
everything right again.

936
00:49:38,584 --> 00:49:40,020
I came back.

937
00:49:40,064 --> 00:49:42,414
I was totally
focused on my family.

938
00:49:44,938 --> 00:49:47,158
I thought having another child
would make Maggie go away

939
00:49:47,201 --> 00:49:49,987
but getting pregnant... Sam...

940
00:49:50,030 --> 00:49:52,380
I think just reinforced
her conviction

941
00:49:52,424 --> 00:49:54,687
that Maggie had made
everything right.

942
00:49:56,776 --> 00:49:59,474
What about Doc and Sam?

943
00:50:05,132 --> 00:50:06,481
I just don't know.

944
00:50:08,614 --> 00:50:10,616
I think Doc's stronger for it.

945
00:50:12,444 --> 00:50:15,142
We're partners.
We talk about it.

946
00:50:15,186 --> 00:50:18,363
If there are scars...
And I look for them,
I don't see them.

947
00:50:19,799 --> 00:50:20,756
Sam?

948
00:50:23,585 --> 00:50:25,283
Sam's okay, for now.

949
00:50:28,025 --> 00:50:29,026
For now.

950
00:50:31,115 --> 00:50:33,117
But, what if...

951
00:50:33,160 --> 00:50:34,292
I mean...

952
00:50:35,162 --> 00:50:36,990
What if...

953
00:50:37,034 --> 00:50:38,774
I'm wrong?

954
00:50:39,688 --> 00:50:40,820
[EXHALES]

955
00:50:42,082 --> 00:50:43,301
Well...

956
00:50:45,520 --> 00:50:47,261
I do ask myself that.

957
00:50:53,006 --> 00:50:54,312
When do you
think it will end?

958
00:50:58,446 --> 00:50:59,665
When Annie says it does.

959
00:51:16,334 --> 00:51:18,118
Come on, Sam.

960
00:51:18,162 --> 00:51:19,815
Whoa!

961
00:51:19,859 --> 00:51:21,469
Hold on, hold on!

962
00:51:21,513 --> 00:51:23,167
[ROLLER COASTER WHOOSHING]

963
00:51:23,210 --> 00:51:24,951
DOC: Doesn't that
look fun, Sam?

964
00:51:26,257 --> 00:51:27,519
[LAUGHING]

965
00:51:29,173 --> 00:51:30,478
MAN: Six to a car.
Watch your step.

966
00:51:31,871 --> 00:51:33,307
Watch your step.

967
00:51:33,351 --> 00:51:34,656
Step right on up.

968
00:51:34,700 --> 00:51:36,136
[KIDS SHOUTING]MAN: All right.

969
00:51:38,443 --> 00:51:40,140
Oh, I'm sorry, Miss.

970
00:51:40,184 --> 00:51:41,924
You're gonna have to
wait down there 'cause
it's six to a row.

971
00:51:41,968 --> 00:51:44,318
Oh.Maggie, you and Gillian
go together, okay, honey?

972
00:51:44,362 --> 00:51:45,363
Come on, Maggie.

973
00:51:47,582 --> 00:51:49,323
[FERRIS WHEEL CREAKING]

974
00:51:52,587 --> 00:51:54,154
Six to a car,
watch your step.

975
00:51:54,198 --> 00:51:55,112
Thank you.

976
00:52:00,552 --> 00:52:01,640
No, uh...

977
00:52:03,685 --> 00:52:05,426
[PEOPLE EXCLAIMING]

978
00:52:07,994 --> 00:52:09,343
[PEOPLE WHOOPING]

979
00:52:11,824 --> 00:52:13,086
[LAUGHING]

980
00:52:14,043 --> 00:52:15,523
Whoo!

981
00:52:23,488 --> 00:52:25,664
DOC: It's beautiful up here.

982
00:52:25,707 --> 00:52:27,187
Look at this.

983
00:52:27,231 --> 00:52:28,536
The beautiful ocean.

984
00:52:28,580 --> 00:52:30,625
So pretty. [LAUGHING]
I love it.

985
00:52:30,669 --> 00:52:31,844
Whoo!

986
00:52:51,168 --> 00:52:52,256
Watch your step.

987
00:52:54,649 --> 00:52:56,651
BOY 1: Pizza!BOY 2: All right.

988
00:53:02,135 --> 00:53:03,441
Where's Maggie?

989
00:53:03,484 --> 00:53:05,094
She, she's right here, Annie.

990
00:53:05,138 --> 00:53:07,184
She was on my lap.
You just didn't see her.

991
00:53:07,227 --> 00:53:09,055
Maggie's lost.
She didn't ride with Gillian.

992
00:53:09,098 --> 00:53:10,752
It's okay, Mom,
we'll find her.

993
00:53:10,796 --> 00:53:12,319
She couldn't
have gone far.

994
00:53:12,363 --> 00:53:14,713
Annie, I, I thought
she was in my lap.

995
00:53:14,756 --> 00:53:15,931
They wouldn't let
her ride in your lap.

996
00:53:15,975 --> 00:53:17,933
Oh, Mom, it's okay...

997
00:53:17,977 --> 00:53:19,108
Don't worry,
I know where she is.

998
00:53:19,152 --> 00:53:20,327
MAN: Is there a problem?

999
00:53:20,371 --> 00:53:21,720
Yeah, my sister wandered away

1000
00:53:21,763 --> 00:53:22,547
but we think we
know where she is.

1001
00:53:22,590 --> 00:53:24,331
What does she look like?

1002
00:53:24,375 --> 00:53:25,854
She's five years old and
she has brown curly hair,

1003
00:53:25,898 --> 00:53:27,291
blue eyes and she's
wearing a jean skirt

1004
00:53:27,334 --> 00:53:29,075
and white sneakers
and her shirt is...

1005
00:53:29,118 --> 00:53:31,860
[SOBBING] I can't remember
what color her shirt is.

1006
00:53:31,904 --> 00:53:34,036
DOC: Um, it's the purple
one with the balloon.

1007
00:53:34,080 --> 00:53:35,429
Are you sure?

1008
00:53:35,473 --> 00:53:37,083
Yeah, 'cause we had
a fight about it.

1009
00:53:37,126 --> 00:53:39,259
She took it out of my
drawer without asking.

1010
00:53:39,303 --> 00:53:41,000
MAN: What's her name?Maggie Beeman.

1011
00:53:41,043 --> 00:53:42,436
MAN: Okay, I'll put it over
the PA system for you.

1012
00:53:42,480 --> 00:53:44,569
Mom, you and Sam stay here.

1013
00:53:44,612 --> 00:53:45,613
Gillian and I will go
find her. Come on.

1014
00:53:46,397 --> 00:53:48,007
Okay.

1015
00:53:48,050 --> 00:53:49,356
[SNIFFLING]

1016
00:53:50,531 --> 00:53:52,054
DOC: This is a first.

1017
00:53:52,098 --> 00:53:53,926
I can't believe it.

1018
00:53:53,969 --> 00:53:55,536
Kids get lost.
I guess it's her turn.

1019
00:53:57,234 --> 00:53:58,235
We found her.

1020
00:53:58,278 --> 00:53:59,366
What?

1021
00:53:59,410 --> 00:54:00,585
Let's go back.

1022
00:54:09,594 --> 00:54:11,596
100 on the nose.

1023
00:54:11,639 --> 00:54:14,163
You got a fever, baby.

1024
00:54:14,207 --> 00:54:15,643
Maybe it's just from
the excitement of the day.

1025
00:54:18,080 --> 00:54:19,691
Well, we'll see.

1026
00:54:19,734 --> 00:54:22,171
Gillian brought you some
tea if you get thirsty.

1027
00:54:22,215 --> 00:54:23,390
With honey.Mmm-hmm.

1028
00:54:28,090 --> 00:54:30,876
Oh... All right, but
I want you to sleep.

1029
00:54:30,919 --> 00:54:32,747
Which one do you want?

1030
00:54:34,358 --> 00:54:36,360
Oh... Gillian,
can you get me

1031
00:54:36,403 --> 00:54:38,318
the  Grandfather Twilight
book over there?

1032
00:54:41,190 --> 00:54:43,889
Thanks. Okay.

1033
00:54:43,932 --> 00:54:46,283
I'll be back in a couple
minutes to hear your prayers.

1034
00:54:47,327 --> 00:54:48,720
Good night, Maggie.

1035
00:54:52,158 --> 00:54:53,899
She'll be all right?

1036
00:54:53,942 --> 00:54:55,770
I think so.

1037
00:54:55,814 --> 00:54:57,511
It's just that she's
getting these so often.

1038
00:54:57,555 --> 00:54:58,773
It's not like her.

1039
00:55:01,559 --> 00:55:04,344
Anyway, uh, let's not
bother Tim with this.

1040
00:55:04,388 --> 00:55:06,215
He would just
worry unnecessarily.

1041
00:55:07,216 --> 00:55:09,697
I'm so sorry...
About today.

1042
00:55:09,741 --> 00:55:10,872
Oh...

1043
00:55:12,744 --> 00:55:15,181
It had a happy ending.
Let it go.

1044
00:55:15,224 --> 00:55:18,315
I was just... [SCOFFS]
Incredibly stupid.

1045
00:55:18,358 --> 00:55:19,664
Oh, let it go, Gilly.

1046
00:55:19,707 --> 00:55:21,448
I have. So has Maggie.

1047
00:55:22,580 --> 00:55:23,711
Okay.

1048
00:55:40,989 --> 00:55:42,513
TIM: Do you like this one?SAM: Yeah.

1049
00:55:42,556 --> 00:55:45,777
TIM: Okay.
We need two more.

