[DOORBELL RINGS]

1052
00:55:49,650 --> 00:55:50,782
I'll get it.

1053
00:55:53,828 --> 00:55:55,134
That's going to go
on top, right?

1054
00:55:55,177 --> 00:55:56,309
Yeah.TIM: Okay.

1055
00:55:58,833 --> 00:56:00,008
WOMAN: Is this the
Beeman residence?

1056
00:56:01,445 --> 00:56:03,403
Um, Gilly?

1057
00:56:03,447 --> 00:56:05,013
Are your parents' home?

1058
00:56:05,057 --> 00:56:06,406
Dad!

1059
00:56:06,450 --> 00:56:07,842
[WHISPERS] Why?

1060
00:56:07,886 --> 00:56:09,888
[RAPID FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1061
00:56:09,931 --> 00:56:12,499
Oh, Annie. Has, has
there been an accident?

1062
00:56:12,543 --> 00:56:15,328
No, everything's fine...
I mean there's been
no accident.

1063
00:56:15,372 --> 00:56:17,199
I'm Marie Tan Lee,

1064
00:56:17,243 --> 00:56:18,766
from the Department of
Children and Family Services.

1065
00:56:21,029 --> 00:56:22,204
Are you Mr. Beeman?

1066
00:56:23,902 --> 00:56:24,642
Yes, I am.

1067
00:56:27,558 --> 00:56:28,863
Could we speak privately?

1068
00:56:32,737 --> 00:56:35,043
Gilly, take the children
in the other room.

1069
00:56:35,696 --> 00:56:36,784
Now.

1070
00:56:46,968 --> 00:56:51,016
Mr. Beeman, we've had a report
of possible irregularities.

1071
00:56:51,059 --> 00:56:52,931
Irregularities? What
the hell does that mean?

1072
00:56:52,974 --> 00:56:55,237
Mr. Beeman, I need to
speak to your children.

1073
00:56:55,281 --> 00:56:56,587
May we come in?My children?

1074
00:56:57,544 --> 00:56:58,632
Yes.

1075
00:56:59,764 --> 00:57:02,201
A report? From whom?

1076
00:57:02,244 --> 00:57:04,899
I'm not at liberty to
say. May we come in?

1077
00:57:04,943 --> 00:57:07,032
I will make this as fast
and painless as I can.

1078
00:57:07,075 --> 00:57:09,295
No.

1079
00:57:09,338 --> 00:57:12,603
These police officers are
here to make sure that I do.

1080
00:57:12,646 --> 00:57:16,041
And that I'm able to
have access to your
children, privately.

1081
00:57:16,084 --> 00:57:19,305
Listen, Miss...
Whoever the hell you are,

1082
00:57:19,348 --> 00:57:21,394
you may not have
access to my children

1083
00:57:21,438 --> 00:57:23,309
and you are not
coming into my house.

1084
00:57:23,352 --> 00:57:26,007
Mr. Beeman, I am coming in.

1085
00:57:26,051 --> 00:57:27,444
That's the law.

1086
00:57:27,487 --> 00:57:29,141
The law?

1087
00:57:29,184 --> 00:57:32,100
Yes. Whenever we have a report
of possible child abuse

1088
00:57:32,144 --> 00:57:36,670
we go to the home involved
to verify the charge or to
dismiss it.

1089
00:57:36,714 --> 00:57:39,760
If I have to, I can come in
here and take your children.

1090
00:57:42,763 --> 00:57:43,895
That's the law, sir.

1091
00:57:47,681 --> 00:57:49,683
Or you can let me in
and let me do my job.

1092
00:57:50,728 --> 00:57:52,425
Well...

1093
00:57:52,469 --> 00:57:53,339
Why do you have
to see them alone?

1094
00:57:54,340 --> 00:57:56,516
Think about it.

1095
00:57:56,560 --> 00:57:59,519
Because of some anonymous
report you claim to have
received?

1096
00:57:59,563 --> 00:58:01,434
I have received.

1097
00:58:01,478 --> 00:58:03,654
Well, who the hell from?
And what abuse?

1098
00:58:03,697 --> 00:58:05,699
I can't tell you.

1099
00:58:05,743 --> 00:58:09,181
The department's policy
protects the identity
of the informants.

1100
00:58:09,224 --> 00:58:10,965
If you let me in
to see your children

1101
00:58:11,009 --> 00:58:13,533
I can determine whether or
not this need go any further.

1102
00:58:13,577 --> 00:58:16,797
If I find no evidence of abuse
this could end right now.

1103
00:58:19,017 --> 00:58:21,498
I'm calling my lawyer.
I don't believe this.

1104
00:58:21,541 --> 00:58:24,152
Call him. You have three
minutes before we come in.

1105
00:58:24,196 --> 00:58:26,372
Please leave the door open
while you make the call.

1106
00:58:42,083 --> 00:58:43,171
Go ahead.

1107
00:58:54,443 --> 00:58:57,055
[LAUGHING]

1108
00:58:57,098 --> 00:58:59,318
It's a very nice room.

1109
00:58:59,361 --> 00:59:01,494
Thanks.[LAUGHING]

1110
00:59:01,538 --> 00:59:02,669
I know whose
room that is.

1111
00:59:02,713 --> 00:59:04,541
That's my room.
Knock, knock.

1112
00:59:04,584 --> 00:59:06,020
Who's there?

1113
00:59:06,064 --> 00:59:07,848
Sack.Sack who?

1114
00:59:07,892 --> 00:59:09,937
Sack of potatoes
from Sacramento.

1115
00:59:09,981 --> 00:59:11,635
[LAUGHING]

1116
00:59:13,985 --> 00:59:15,464
Whose room is this?

1117
00:59:15,508 --> 00:59:16,814
DOC: It's, um, uh...

1118
00:59:16,857 --> 00:59:17,945
SAM: This is Maggie's room.

1119
00:59:19,512 --> 00:59:20,295
So.

1120
00:59:22,994 --> 00:59:25,170
You'll be hearing from us.
Goodbye, guys.

1121
00:59:25,213 --> 00:59:26,954
What does that mean?

1122
00:59:26,998 --> 00:59:28,434
Thank you, Mr. Beeman.

1123
00:59:32,786 --> 00:59:35,833
[HORNS HONKING]

1124
00:59:36,964 --> 00:59:38,662
Tim, is everything okay?

1125
00:59:38,705 --> 00:59:40,620
TIM: [OVER PHONE] 
Yeah, it's fine. 
Where are you?

1126
00:59:40,664 --> 00:59:43,275
Stuck in traffic. Are you
sure everything's okay?

1127
00:59:43,318 --> 00:59:45,016
TIM:  Annie, what is this? 
We're fine.

1128
00:59:45,059 --> 00:59:46,495
[SIGHS]

1129
00:59:46,539 --> 00:59:47,888
I had the strangest feeling.

1130
00:59:47,932 --> 00:59:49,629
TIM:  Look, just come home.

1131
00:59:49,673 --> 00:59:50,630
We're fine.

1132
00:59:50,674 --> 00:59:53,415
Okay. Love you.

1133
00:59:53,459 --> 00:59:54,939
TIM:  Me, too.[DISCONNECTS CALL]

1134
00:59:56,984 --> 00:59:58,551
Well, I guess they're fine.

1135
01:00:01,685 --> 01:00:03,338
Oh, honey, you're burning up.

1136
01:00:09,518 --> 01:00:11,433
[WEEPING QUIETLY]

1137
01:00:11,477 --> 01:00:12,696
[KNOCK AT DOOR]

1138
01:00:12,739 --> 01:00:13,827
Gillian.

1139
01:00:14,741 --> 01:00:16,525
GILLIAN: I'm so...

1140
01:00:16,569 --> 01:00:19,006
I'm the person who
talked to them.

1141
01:00:19,050 --> 01:00:20,442
It's all my fault.

1142
01:00:20,486 --> 01:00:22,053
I believe you.
What did you do?

1143
01:00:23,445 --> 01:00:24,577
I...

1144
01:00:25,883 --> 01:00:27,580
When did you do it?

1145
01:00:27,624 --> 01:00:29,408
Two months ago.

1146
01:00:29,451 --> 01:00:32,367
It was before you explained
everything to me that night.

1147
01:00:32,411 --> 01:00:34,369
I, I never thought
they'd come here.

1148
01:00:34,413 --> 01:00:36,937
Oh, God, it was
just so awful.

1149
01:00:36,981 --> 01:00:39,766
Yes, it was.
What did you do?

1150
01:00:39,810 --> 01:00:41,725
I went to one of those
psychiatrist people.

1151
01:00:43,074 --> 01:00:45,337
You saw a psychiatrist, and...

1152
01:00:45,380 --> 01:00:46,947
He said that Doc was fine

1153
01:00:46,991 --> 01:00:48,732
because she knew that
Maggie was a fiction.

1154
01:00:50,124 --> 01:00:51,386
But to worry about Sam.

1155
01:00:51,430 --> 01:00:53,475
And, you didn't
want to tell me.

1156
01:00:53,519 --> 01:00:55,042
No, because...Because I was part of it.

1157
01:00:58,480 --> 01:01:01,353
So, then you went to the
Child Services Office.
Again, instead of me.

1158
01:01:01,396 --> 01:01:03,660
I thought that they
might be able...

1159
01:01:03,703 --> 01:01:05,574
But she was so horrible,
and I left.

1160
01:01:05,618 --> 01:01:08,186
I was, I was angry and
frightened and I walked away

1161
01:01:08,229 --> 01:01:11,842
and I never, never thought
she would do anything.

1162
01:01:11,885 --> 01:01:13,452
You saw that woman
who was here?

1163
01:01:15,759 --> 01:01:17,064
What did you tell her?

1164
01:01:20,807 --> 01:01:24,550
You told her that Annie thinks
she has an invisible daughter.

1165
01:01:26,334 --> 01:01:28,423
That I forced Doc into
playing along with it

1166
01:01:28,467 --> 01:01:31,383
and that Sam has spent
his entire life around
this insanity.

1167
01:01:31,426 --> 01:01:33,167
I know now
that that was wrong.
I love you all.

1168
01:01:33,211 --> 01:01:34,168
I was wrong.

1169
01:01:35,430 --> 01:01:36,997
Were you?

1170
01:01:37,041 --> 01:01:39,173
Yes! It's just what you think
if you don't understand.

1171
01:01:39,217 --> 01:01:41,175
That's comforting.

1172
01:01:41,219 --> 01:01:42,568
But those people
in Child Services

1173
01:01:42,611 --> 01:01:43,612
are not going to understand.

1174
01:01:43,656 --> 01:01:45,092
I know.

1175
01:01:45,136 --> 01:01:48,400
And I'm, I'm so sorry.

1176
01:01:48,443 --> 01:01:49,618
I'm leaving.You're not leaving.

1177
01:01:52,534 --> 01:01:54,406
Why?

1178
01:01:54,449 --> 01:01:55,799
Because you're going
to help me fix this.

1179
01:02:13,817 --> 01:02:16,036
DOC:  Dad? 
What can they do?

1180
01:02:18,735 --> 01:02:20,084
Nothing.

1181
01:02:21,172 --> 01:02:22,826
I don't know.

1182
01:02:22,869 --> 01:02:26,612
If she can walk in with
two cops, that was gross.

1183
01:02:26,655 --> 01:02:28,440
It was gross.

1184
01:02:28,483 --> 01:02:30,007
How'd they know
about Maggie?

1185
01:02:30,921 --> 01:02:32,096
It doesn't matter.

1186
01:02:32,879 --> 01:02:34,707
It was Gillian. I hate her.

1187
01:02:34,751 --> 01:02:36,753
TIM: No, you don't.

1188
01:02:36,796 --> 01:02:38,145
She loves you.

1189
01:02:39,407 --> 01:02:42,062
Doc... Everybody
makes mistakes.

1190
01:02:43,107 --> 01:02:44,499
And you love her.

1191
01:02:44,543 --> 01:02:46,110
Not anymore.

1192
01:02:46,153 --> 01:02:48,025
She's going to help
make this right.

1193
01:02:50,114 --> 01:02:51,506
But what can they do,
take us away?

1194
01:02:51,550 --> 01:02:52,943
No!

1195
01:02:54,292 --> 01:02:55,946
Let's run away.

1196
01:02:55,989 --> 01:02:58,122
Well, there's an idea.

1197
01:02:58,165 --> 01:03:00,515
How about an island
in the South Pacific?

1198
01:03:00,559 --> 01:03:02,169
Come on, let's do it.

1199
01:03:02,213 --> 01:03:03,692
We'll leave tonight.

1200
01:03:03,736 --> 01:03:06,130
Mom and you and me and Sam.
Not Gillian.

1201
01:03:06,173 --> 01:03:10,830
Honey, they can't do
anything to us, I promise.

1202
01:03:10,874 --> 01:03:13,050
But what if they do?
What if they try
to take us away?

1203
01:03:15,052 --> 01:03:17,010
Then we run away.

1204
01:03:17,054 --> 01:03:20,361
Well, what if they come
with tanks and more cops
and all that?

1205
01:03:21,362 --> 01:03:22,668
We sneak out the back

1206
01:03:22,711 --> 01:03:24,452
right down to the boat
in the open sea.

1207
01:03:25,845 --> 01:03:27,238
You promise?

1208
01:03:27,281 --> 01:03:28,195
I promise.

1209
01:03:30,894 --> 01:03:33,244
ANNIE: Tim?

1210
01:03:33,287 --> 01:03:35,115
Tim, call the doctor.
Maggie's really sick.

1211
01:03:37,074 --> 01:03:39,772
Annie, slow down.
If she needs a doctor

1212
01:03:39,816 --> 01:03:40,904
I'll take her to him,
like I always do.

1213
01:03:40,947 --> 01:03:42,644
No, um, she's too
sick to move.

1214
01:03:42,688 --> 01:03:44,342
My God, he'll
make a house call.

1215
01:03:44,385 --> 01:03:46,126
He's been her doctor
her whole life.

1216
01:03:46,170 --> 01:03:48,128
I don't know.
We'll see, okay?Please.

1217
01:03:48,172 --> 01:03:49,913
DOC: Are you all right?Hmm-mmm.

1218
01:03:49,956 --> 01:03:51,349
It's going to be okay.

1219
01:03:54,439 --> 01:03:55,527
It's going to be okay.

1220
01:04:02,055 --> 01:04:04,231
He wasn't available. I'll
just take her to the hospital.

1221
01:04:04,275 --> 01:04:05,667
I'm going.Honey, you don't have to.

1222
01:04:05,711 --> 01:04:07,365
I know.

1223
01:04:07,408 --> 01:04:10,063
Gillian, can you help
me get Maggie dressed?

1224
01:04:10,107 --> 01:04:11,369
We're taking her
to the hospital.

1225
01:04:16,113 --> 01:04:17,462
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

1226
01:04:18,811 --> 01:04:20,160
Okay, honey.

1227
01:04:23,947 --> 01:04:25,862
WOMAN: [OVER INTERCOM] 
Dr. Grace to room 305.

1228
01:04:25,905 --> 01:04:27,907
Dr. Grace to room 305, please.

1229
01:04:31,041 --> 01:04:32,303
[PHONE RINGING]

1230
01:04:34,696 --> 01:04:36,960
TIM: Honey, you're going
to sit here and I'll go
talk to the nurse.

1231
01:04:42,879 --> 01:04:46,143
Oh, don't worry, honey.
Daddy will be right back.

1232
01:04:46,186 --> 01:04:47,361
Everything's going
to be fine.

1233
01:04:48,928 --> 01:04:50,582
May I help you?

1234
01:04:50,625 --> 01:04:53,715
Yes, I, I have this
pain in my stomach

1235
01:04:53,759 --> 01:04:55,282
and I'm worried it
might be an ulcer.

1236
01:04:55,326 --> 01:04:57,023
Well, we can take a look.

1237
01:04:57,067 --> 01:04:58,372
Do you have insurance?

1238
01:04:58,895 --> 01:05:00,244
Yes.

1239
01:05:09,688 --> 01:05:11,168
Have you read this yet?

1240
01:05:18,088 --> 01:05:20,917
Here's one I've never heard
of before... Seismosaurus.

1241
01:05:23,267 --> 01:05:24,529
There's T-Rex.

1242
01:05:26,139 --> 01:05:27,227
Mr. Beeman?

1243
01:05:28,925 --> 01:05:30,578
Oh, wouldn't you
rather Mommy wait here

1244
01:05:30,622 --> 01:05:31,840
and when you come back,
you'll be all better?

1245
01:05:33,277 --> 01:05:35,801
Good. It'll be
okay, honey.

1246
01:05:35,844 --> 01:05:37,846
No. Tim, I want to come.

1247
01:05:37,890 --> 01:05:40,023
Well, two to one, outvoted.

1248
01:05:46,638 --> 01:05:48,683
I understand you
have stomach pain.

1249
01:05:48,727 --> 01:05:49,946
I... Do, yes.

1250
01:05:49,989 --> 01:05:50,947
Where?

1251
01:05:51,730 --> 01:05:52,992
Uh...

1252
01:05:53,036 --> 01:05:54,820
Here.

1253
01:05:54,863 --> 01:05:56,300
Could you remove
your shirt, please?

1254
01:06:07,093 --> 01:06:10,183
Well, I had this fever
just 24 hours ago

1255
01:06:10,227 --> 01:06:13,012
and, and I didn't
call my doctor.

1256
01:06:13,056 --> 01:06:15,928
Now the fever's gone,
but this pain in my stomach

1257
01:06:15,972 --> 01:06:18,017
I just thought
it might be related.

1258
01:06:18,061 --> 01:06:19,497
DOCTOR: Really?

1259
01:06:20,280 --> 01:06:22,587
Hmm...

1260
01:06:22,630 --> 01:06:25,677
Well, that's pretty
interesting, Mr. Beeman
but honestly, you seem fine.

1261
01:06:26,721 --> 01:06:28,158
I mean, I believe you...

1262
01:06:28,201 --> 01:06:29,986
Uh-huh.

1263
01:06:30,029 --> 01:06:31,422
If your stomach hurts
your stomach hurts.

1264
01:06:31,465 --> 01:06:32,423
Right.

1265
01:06:34,642 --> 01:06:37,471
Then again, it could
all be in your mind.

1266
01:06:38,690 --> 01:06:39,952
Really?

1267
01:06:41,388 --> 01:06:44,522
Well...
Hope you feel better.

1268
01:06:44,565 --> 01:06:46,263
Thanks. I'm really
glad I came.

1269
01:06:47,873 --> 01:06:50,223
Uh, Doctor, excuse me.Yes?

1270
01:06:50,267 --> 01:06:52,704
Um, could I have, uh,
one of those lollipops?

1271
01:06:54,662 --> 01:06:56,795
Uh... Yeah.

1272
01:06:56,838 --> 01:06:58,362
Sure, I guess so.

1273
01:06:59,406 --> 01:07:00,886
I have a daughter out front.

1274
01:07:01,669 --> 01:07:02,888
Of course.

1275
01:07:04,890 --> 01:07:05,891
Thanks.

1276
01:07:07,849 --> 01:07:10,461
TIM: Nice doctor.
It's nothing worry about.

1277
01:07:10,504 --> 01:07:12,158
Oh, Maggie, you look better.

1278
01:07:12,202 --> 01:07:13,420
Was there a prescription?

1279
01:07:13,464 --> 01:07:16,902
The usual. Aspirin, fluids.

1280
01:07:16,945 --> 01:07:19,426
Everything's going
to be okay. Come on.

1281
01:07:50,849 --> 01:07:52,807
Tim?[GASPS]

1282
01:07:52,851 --> 01:07:54,244
I'm sorry.

1283
01:07:54,287 --> 01:07:55,375
You startled me,
that's all.

1284
01:07:56,420 --> 01:07:57,725
Are you okay?

1285
01:07:59,553 --> 01:08:01,164
I remember the day
I first saw you.

1286
01:08:02,643 --> 01:08:03,775
Oh, God.

1287
01:08:09,520 --> 01:08:10,825
I'd do anything for you.

1288
01:08:13,306 --> 01:08:16,483
Tim. You're shaking.

1289
01:08:16,527 --> 01:08:18,485
Anything, Annie.

1290
01:08:18,529 --> 01:08:20,139
Are you worried
about Maggie?

1291
01:08:20,183 --> 01:08:21,749
No. No, it's just...
[EXHALES]

1292
01:08:23,011 --> 01:08:24,578
I don't know
how to express it.

1293
01:08:27,451 --> 01:08:28,800
I want...

1294
01:08:28,843 --> 01:08:31,063
I want to take care of you.

1295
01:08:31,107 --> 01:08:33,152
I want to tell you
how much I love you.

1296
01:08:34,762 --> 01:08:36,329
I love our family.

1297
01:09:06,359 --> 01:09:07,969
DOC: Hey, Gilly.

1298
01:09:08,013 --> 01:09:08,970
Can I come in?

1299
01:09:09,014 --> 01:09:10,146
Sure.

1300
01:09:17,022 --> 01:09:19,677
What's the matter?

1301
01:09:19,720 --> 01:09:23,376
Oh, it's... Our going
to see that woman at
Children's Services today.

1302
01:09:23,420 --> 01:09:25,117
I guess I'm just frightened.

1303
01:09:27,598 --> 01:09:29,643
Does your mother know,
do you think?

1304
01:09:30,340 --> 01:09:31,950
No. She doesn't.

1305
01:09:31,993 --> 01:09:32,864
I'd know.

1306
01:09:34,648 --> 01:09:37,303
God, this is just so awful.

1307
01:09:39,175 --> 01:09:41,525
Come on, there's
nothing to worry about.

1308
01:09:41,568 --> 01:09:42,961
You're going to be great.

1309
01:09:43,004 --> 01:09:44,092
You're so sure.

1310
01:09:44,876 --> 01:09:45,877
Mostly.

1311
01:09:46,791 --> 01:09:48,009
I hope you're right.

1312
01:09:50,055 --> 01:09:52,231
Well, like Dad said

1313
01:09:52,275 --> 01:09:54,451
if anything does happen
we just run away.

1314
01:09:54,494 --> 01:09:55,539
Run away?

1315
01:09:56,366 --> 01:09:57,758
He said that?

1316
01:09:57,802 --> 01:09:59,325
Yeah.

1317
01:09:59,369 --> 01:10:01,153
He said we'd run away
to the South Pacific.

1318
01:10:03,329 --> 01:10:05,113
[SOBBING] I don't
want to run away.

1319
01:10:05,157 --> 01:10:06,332
Sweetheart.

1320
01:10:06,376 --> 01:10:08,987
[SOBBING]Shh...

1321
01:10:11,859 --> 01:10:13,034
[SOBBING]
I don't want to...

1322
01:10:13,078 --> 01:10:14,906
Shh... Oh, Doc.

1323
01:10:16,473 --> 01:10:18,562
Everything's going
to be fine, I promise.

1324
01:10:28,136 --> 01:10:29,790
LEE: Mr. Beeman,
you may come in now.

1325
01:10:40,236 --> 01:10:42,934
This is Mr. Beeman.

1326
01:10:42,977 --> 01:10:45,850
Mr. Beeman, this is
Mrs. Carperhorn
and Mr. Schmidlen.

1327
01:11:02,475 --> 01:11:05,261
I have a lawsuit in here.

1328
01:11:05,304 --> 01:11:07,263
You invade my home
with armed policemen

1329
01:11:07,306 --> 01:11:09,961
threaten me with
insubstantial evidence,

1330
01:11:10,004 --> 01:11:12,877
talk to my children alone.
About what, I don't know.

1331
01:11:12,920 --> 01:11:15,183
Then send a letter threatening
to take my children away

1332
01:11:15,227 --> 01:11:17,621
if I don't appear today
for this meeting.

1333
01:11:17,664 --> 01:11:22,452
This isn't even a courtroom
and I could lose my family?

1334
01:11:22,495 --> 01:11:26,194
I hope you've prepared
well because I don't
intend to stay here long.

1335
01:11:26,238 --> 01:11:29,676
I'm sorry you feel
that way, Mr. Beeman
but, where's your wife?

1336
01:11:29,720 --> 01:11:31,504
Her presence was requested.

1337
01:11:31,548 --> 01:11:33,201
My wife is at home, sick.

1338
01:11:34,768 --> 01:11:37,336
Your wife is the crux
of this thing, Mr. Beeman.

1339
01:11:37,380 --> 01:11:41,035
The allegation is
that she believes she
has a nonexistent child

1340
01:11:41,079 --> 01:11:42,907
and that you support
her in this fantasy.

1341
01:11:43,777 --> 01:11:46,040
That's ludicrous.

1342
01:11:46,084 --> 01:11:47,825
Where is your wife?I just told you.

1343
01:11:50,741 --> 01:11:52,308
What about your son?
We want to talk to him.

1344
01:11:53,439 --> 01:11:54,658
I brought my daughter.

1345
01:11:56,573 --> 01:11:58,139
It kills me that she has
to go through this again

1346
01:11:58,183 --> 01:11:59,880
and I'm allowing it,
but that's it.

1347
01:12:01,273 --> 01:12:02,405
You've got our nanny.

1348
01:12:02,448 --> 01:12:04,102
You can see her alone, too.

1349
01:12:04,145 --> 01:12:05,843
She's with us
all day, every day.

1350
01:12:05,886 --> 01:12:08,280
Ask her whatever you like.

1351
01:12:08,324 --> 01:12:11,501
And you can talk to my
daughter. Which I hate!

1352
01:12:11,544 --> 01:12:15,200
But you are not
talking to my son.

1353
01:12:15,243 --> 01:12:18,421
He's in school.
My wife is sick.

1354
01:12:18,464 --> 01:12:20,858
Are we clear on this?
Because if we aren't

1355
01:12:20,901 --> 01:12:24,296
and you come back into my life
after today, believe me...

1356
01:12:25,950 --> 01:12:26,864
You don't know
what trouble is.

1357
01:12:31,390 --> 01:12:33,784
Anything else?

1358
01:12:33,827 --> 01:12:35,786
We all understand
your attitude.

1359
01:12:35,829 --> 01:12:37,004
We'll talk to your nanny now.

1360
01:12:43,446 --> 01:12:45,752
LEE: Now, Gillian, we
know between ourselves,

1361
01:12:45,796 --> 01:12:48,146
that you're the one that
started these allegations.

1362
01:12:48,189 --> 01:12:50,235
No, I didn't.

1363
01:12:50,278 --> 01:12:52,237
Excuse me?

1364
01:12:52,280 --> 01:12:54,718
Well, I, I mean I did come
to see you, that's true,

1365
01:12:54,761 --> 01:12:57,285
because there was a nanny,

1366
01:12:57,329 --> 01:12:58,678
a friend of mine
from the playground

1367
01:12:58,722 --> 01:13:01,072
and she had a problem...

1368
01:13:01,115 --> 01:13:02,639
She's Irish, actually...

1369
01:13:02,682 --> 01:13:03,814
And she was a
little frightened.

1370
01:13:03,857 --> 01:13:05,337
So I, I said I would come here

1371
01:13:05,381 --> 01:13:07,948
and try and find out
some information for her.

1372
01:13:07,992 --> 01:13:12,475
So, I did explain to you
or at least I, I started to

1373
01:13:12,518 --> 01:13:14,433
a situation that she was
dealing with in her home

1374
01:13:14,477 --> 01:13:16,827
but it was obvious
you couldn't help.

1375
01:13:16,870 --> 01:13:18,524
So I left.

1376
01:13:18,568 --> 01:13:23,616
And where this nonsense
comes from, I don't know.

1377
01:13:23,660 --> 01:13:25,749
That's not true
and you know it.

1378
01:13:26,532 --> 01:13:29,056
What's not true?

1379
01:13:29,100 --> 01:13:31,537
You told me a story of
a seriously disturbed woman.

1380
01:13:31,581 --> 01:13:33,278
A mother of two small children

1381
01:13:33,321 --> 01:13:35,193
who believes that she has
a third invisible child.

1382
01:13:39,415 --> 01:13:40,416
Do you honestly deny that?

1383
01:13:42,287 --> 01:13:44,463
That's the oddest thing
I've ever heard

1384
01:13:44,507 --> 01:13:46,596
and, yes, I deny it.

1385
01:13:54,691 --> 01:13:56,214
How are you, Rebecca?

1386
01:13:56,257 --> 01:13:57,694
Fine, thank you.
Why am I here?

1387
01:13:58,825 --> 01:14:00,653
Some children need protecting.

1388
01:14:00,697 --> 01:14:02,394
That's why we're here.

1389
01:14:02,438 --> 01:14:05,441
So, don't be afraid to
say anything you want.

1390
01:14:05,484 --> 01:14:06,920
We're on your side.

1391
01:14:06,964 --> 01:14:07,965
Uh-huh.

1392
01:14:10,054 --> 01:14:12,273
Now, this thing that we
talked about before, um,

1393
01:14:12,317 --> 01:14:14,101
your invisible sister...

1394
01:14:14,145 --> 01:14:15,538
Invisible sister?

1395
01:14:16,800 --> 01:14:19,498
You have an invisible sister.

1396
01:14:19,542 --> 01:14:22,066
My brother has an
imaginary friend or two.

1397
01:14:22,109 --> 01:14:23,850
We call one Maggie.
Is that what you mean?

1398
01:14:25,591 --> 01:14:29,203
Actually, Maggie was my
invisible friend before
she was his.

1399
01:14:29,247 --> 01:14:30,553
It was kind of like
the tooth fairy.

1400
01:14:30,596 --> 01:14:32,468
You grow out of it.

1401
01:14:32,511 --> 01:14:34,992
Or, do you still believe
in the Tooth Fairy?

1402
01:14:36,210 --> 01:14:37,603
No.

1403
01:14:37,647 --> 01:14:39,257
DOC: Me, neither.

1404
01:14:39,300 --> 01:14:41,389
So anyway, I grew
out of Maggie.

1405
01:14:41,433 --> 01:14:42,913
It was fun.

1406
01:14:42,956 --> 01:14:45,306
But Sam, he liked her.

1407
01:14:45,350 --> 01:14:48,222
So, now Sam's got
Maggie for a while.

1408
01:14:48,266 --> 01:14:50,877
You see, Sam
believes in Santa Claus,

1409
01:14:50,921 --> 01:14:53,489
the Easter Bunny, the
Tooth Fairy, and Maggie.

1410
01:14:54,838 --> 01:14:56,535
You think I should tell him

1411
01:14:56,579 --> 01:14:58,015
about Santa Claus
and everything.

1412
01:14:58,058 --> 01:14:59,233
Is that why I'm here?

1413
01:14:59,277 --> 01:15:01,322
No.

1414
01:15:01,366 --> 01:15:02,759
We're trying to determine

1415
01:15:02,802 --> 01:15:04,804
if you and your brother
are in a safe environment.

1416
01:15:06,066 --> 01:15:07,285
We're fine.

1417
01:15:08,939 --> 01:15:10,767
Isn't it true that
your mother thinks

1418
01:15:10,810 --> 01:15:12,856
she has an
invisible daughter

1419
01:15:12,899 --> 01:15:16,250
and that you and your father
help her with this fantasy?

1420
01:15:16,294 --> 01:15:18,862
[LAUGHS]

1421
01:15:18,905 --> 01:15:21,691
No. Do you know...
See, this is weird.

1422
01:15:21,734 --> 01:15:25,390
See... I don't even
like knowing there's
no Santa Claus.

1423
01:15:25,433 --> 01:15:27,479
So, every year, I help
my mom and dad

1424
01:15:27,523 --> 01:15:29,568
fool Sam into thinking
there is a Santa Claus.

1425
01:15:29,612 --> 01:15:30,787
[SIGHS]

1426
01:15:30,830 --> 01:15:32,615
So, we all play
along with Maggie

1427
01:15:32,658 --> 01:15:34,573
like we play along
with Santa Claus.

1428
01:15:34,617 --> 01:15:36,923
There is a big difference
between Santa Claus,

1429
01:15:36,967 --> 01:15:39,099
the Easter Bunny,
the Tooth Fairy

1430
01:15:39,143 --> 01:15:42,189
and a particular fantasy
that nobody else has,

1431
01:15:42,233 --> 01:15:43,539
like a sister
who doesn't exist.

1432
01:15:44,931 --> 01:15:46,629
Really?

1433
01:15:46,672 --> 01:15:48,456
She's not a sister.

1434
01:15:48,500 --> 01:15:51,068
But that's a good idea!
She could be.

1435
01:15:51,111 --> 01:15:54,593
Santa Claus is an established
cultural fantasy.

1436
01:15:54,637 --> 01:15:57,553
Now, when somebody has a
fantasy that nobody else does,

1437
01:15:57,596 --> 01:15:59,511
Rebecca, that's a
very different thing.

1438
01:16:00,730 --> 01:16:01,992
Oh.

1439
01:16:03,515 --> 01:16:04,995
Like Martin Luther King.

1440
01:16:06,257 --> 01:16:07,824
We studied him.

1441
01:16:07,867 --> 01:16:10,174
He had a dream.
No one else had it.

1442
01:16:10,217 --> 01:16:13,438
No, not like him.
Like craziness...

1443
01:16:13,481 --> 01:16:16,006
Santa Claus is sort of
crazy if you think about it.

1444
01:16:16,049 --> 01:16:18,225
I mean, come on. One guy
for the whole world,

1445
01:16:18,269 --> 01:16:19,139
in one night?

1446
01:16:20,532 --> 01:16:23,187
And the thing is,
I got to tell you

1447
01:16:23,230 --> 01:16:26,016
even though I know
there's no Santa Claus,

1448
01:16:26,059 --> 01:16:28,584
I still kind
of believe in him.

1449
01:16:28,627 --> 01:16:30,324
I don't even tell
my parents this.

1450
01:16:30,368 --> 01:16:31,630
You won't tell them, will you?

1451
01:16:34,415 --> 01:16:36,243
So, when we're putting out
the milk and cookies and stuff

1452
01:16:36,287 --> 01:16:38,158
that I know Dad's going to eat

1453
01:16:38,202 --> 01:16:39,420
and the carrot
for the reindeer,

1454
01:16:39,464 --> 01:16:41,684
that I know Mom's going to eat

1455
01:16:41,727 --> 01:16:44,164
I still believe he's
out there somewhere.

1456
01:16:46,645 --> 01:16:48,560
I believe in Peter Pan, too.

1457
01:16:53,086 --> 01:16:54,914
So, what are we going to do?

1458
01:16:54,958 --> 01:16:56,742
Maggie's fun. Is that bad?

1459
01:17:00,398 --> 01:17:03,096
Could you, um, ask your
father to come back in?

1460
01:17:04,445 --> 01:17:05,577
Sure.

1461
01:17:09,146 --> 01:17:12,584
Mr. Beeman, your daughter
is quite impressive.

1462
01:17:12,628 --> 01:17:15,543
It appears that
there's been some mistake.

1463
01:17:15,587 --> 01:17:18,677
I hope you understand
that our motives are
to protect the children.

1464
01:17:18,721 --> 01:17:19,809
That's why we're here.

1465
01:17:20,374 --> 01:17:22,899
I do.

1466
01:17:22,942 --> 01:17:24,596
And I'm sorry
about my temper.

1467
01:17:27,730 --> 01:17:30,080
I'm glad you people are here
for the people who need you.

1468
01:17:31,777 --> 01:17:33,126
I'm glad we don't.

1469
01:17:42,875 --> 01:17:44,398
[ALL CHEERING]

1470
01:17:44,442 --> 01:17:45,791
[LAUGHING]

1471
01:17:45,835 --> 01:17:48,315
[SIGHS]

1472
01:17:48,359 --> 01:17:50,666
Doc, there's something
I have to tell you.

1473
01:17:51,623 --> 01:17:53,146
It was me.

1474
01:17:53,190 --> 01:17:54,495
I'm the one who
caused all of this.

1475
01:17:54,539 --> 01:17:55,888
I'm, I'm sorry.

1476
01:17:55,932 --> 01:17:57,847
I knew that.

1477
01:17:57,890 --> 01:17:59,283
Everyone makes mistakes.

1478
01:18:00,763 --> 01:18:03,156
Race you to the car![LAUGHS]

