01:18:42,239 --> 01:18:44,589
Mom! Mommy, look.Here she is.

1501
01:18:44,632 --> 01:18:45,938
One, two, three...

1502
01:18:45,982 --> 01:18:49,115
ALL: Happy un-birthday![DOC LAUGHING]

1503
01:18:49,159 --> 01:18:50,769
Aren't you supposed
to be in school?

1504
01:18:50,813 --> 01:18:52,336
Well, Doc and I
were playing hooky

1505
01:18:52,379 --> 01:18:53,816
and we ran into Gilly
doing her errands

1506
01:18:53,859 --> 01:18:55,992
and, uh, we all decided
to take the day off.

1507
01:18:56,035 --> 01:18:57,297
And we got you
something. Look!

1508
01:18:57,341 --> 01:18:58,342
Oh!

1509
01:19:02,650 --> 01:19:04,391
It's a horse.
A really old horse.

1510
01:19:04,435 --> 01:19:06,611
Oh, it's a beautiful horse.

1511
01:19:07,917 --> 01:19:09,092
Thank you.

1512
01:19:11,834 --> 01:19:13,009
TIM: What's wrong?

1513
01:19:14,532 --> 01:19:16,099
Maggie's sicker,
a lot sicker.

1514
01:19:16,142 --> 01:19:18,275
I'm doing what
the doctor said.

1515
01:19:18,318 --> 01:19:19,798
The fever is back.

1516
01:19:19,842 --> 01:19:21,626
TIM: Do you want to go
back to the hospital?

1517
01:19:21,669 --> 01:19:22,975
I don't know.

1518
01:19:24,281 --> 01:19:25,325
Not now.

1519
01:19:27,980 --> 01:19:31,723
Um, could we put
this in her room?

1520
01:19:31,767 --> 01:19:34,117
I mean, would you all mind
telling her that it's for her?

1521
01:19:34,160 --> 01:19:35,596
DOC: No, no.TIM: Of course not.

1522
01:19:44,997 --> 01:19:46,738
[SCRIBBLING]

1523
01:19:48,914 --> 01:19:50,350
What is it?

1524
01:19:50,394 --> 01:19:52,265
Maggie.

1525
01:19:52,309 --> 01:19:53,527
I'm really worried.

1526
01:19:55,834 --> 01:19:57,662
Maggie lives in
Annie, remember?

1527
01:19:57,705 --> 01:19:59,403
Yeah.

1528
01:19:59,446 --> 01:20:01,100
I just feel so helpless.

1529
01:20:02,145 --> 01:20:03,102
We are.

1530
01:20:06,323 --> 01:20:07,933
Annie has all the controls.

1531
01:20:09,456 --> 01:20:11,197
And, when you love someone

1532
01:20:12,285 --> 01:20:13,547
you are...

1533
01:20:14,766 --> 01:20:16,159
Totally vulnerable.

1534
01:20:18,291 --> 01:20:19,640
Children teach you that.

1535
01:20:25,559 --> 01:20:26,604
[WHISPERING] What?

1536
01:20:28,432 --> 01:20:29,607
A, a what?

1537
01:20:31,435 --> 01:20:32,392
Where?

1538
01:20:33,089 --> 01:20:34,481
Can you point?

1539
01:20:40,705 --> 01:20:42,098
I can't see it.

1540
01:20:43,708 --> 01:20:45,971
Must be a beautiful angel.

1541
01:20:46,015 --> 01:20:48,495
[SNIFFLES]
And it must be just for you.

1542
01:20:52,935 --> 01:20:55,372
Mom, I made you something
in school today.

1543
01:20:55,415 --> 01:20:57,200
Oh. [SNIFFLES]

1544
01:20:57,243 --> 01:20:59,985
Look at that.

1545
01:21:00,029 --> 01:21:02,640
What is it?It's a turtle
made out of clay.

1546
01:21:02,683 --> 01:21:04,381
[SOFTLY] Aw...

1547
01:21:04,424 --> 01:21:06,339
I'm going to
paint it tomorrow.

1548
01:21:06,383 --> 01:21:09,168
But I could give it
to you unpainted.

1549
01:21:09,212 --> 01:21:11,518
Painting it would be nice.

1550
01:21:11,562 --> 01:21:13,607
You look sad.
Is Maggie okay?

1551
01:21:16,175 --> 01:21:17,873
Oh, she's a little sick.

1552
01:21:20,092 --> 01:21:22,965
Hi, Maggie.
I made something for you, too.

1553
01:21:25,097 --> 01:21:28,709
Actually, Mom, could
I give yours to Maggie?

1554
01:21:28,753 --> 01:21:30,363
Of course.

1555
01:21:32,626 --> 01:21:33,932
Here, Maggie.

1556
01:21:35,325 --> 01:21:36,456
[SNIFFLES] Hey, Sam.

1557
01:21:38,850 --> 01:21:40,852
Maggie saw an angel
up there in the corner.

1558
01:21:42,288 --> 01:21:43,681
Do you see it?

1559
01:21:46,336 --> 01:21:48,338
Yeah, I see it.

1560
01:21:48,381 --> 01:21:50,731
Yeah, I think I see it.

1561
01:21:50,775 --> 01:21:52,168
Yeah, I see it!

1562
01:21:56,172 --> 01:21:58,652
Is Maggie contagious?

1563
01:21:58,696 --> 01:22:00,176
No, honey, she's not.

1564
01:22:02,918 --> 01:22:05,007
Is Maggie going
to feel better soon?

1565
01:22:06,095 --> 01:22:07,357
I don't know.

1566
01:22:07,400 --> 01:22:08,749
'Cause I told my teacher

1567
01:22:08,793 --> 01:22:11,100
I would like to bring
Maggie for show-and-tell.

1568
01:22:11,143 --> 01:22:13,363
Show-and-tell Maggie.

1569
01:22:13,406 --> 01:22:15,278
She could just
walk down the hall.

1570
01:22:15,321 --> 01:22:16,279
And she said, "Yes."

1571
01:22:18,803 --> 01:22:21,240
Well... She has
to get better first.

1572
01:22:23,677 --> 01:22:25,244
Okay...

1573
01:22:25,288 --> 01:22:27,594
Let's leave Maggie alone
with her angel, okay?

1574
01:22:33,426 --> 01:22:34,688
[LAUGHING]

1575
01:22:34,732 --> 01:22:36,342
You know what?
Can't be trusted.

1576
01:22:36,386 --> 01:22:37,735
Cannot be trusted.[DOC EXCLAIMS]

1577
01:22:37,778 --> 01:22:38,866
SAM: Hey, Dad!

1578
01:22:38,910 --> 01:22:40,172
[DOC LAUGHS]

1579
01:22:40,216 --> 01:22:41,739
ANNIE: Smells great.

1580
01:22:41,782 --> 01:22:43,523
Maggie's coming to
show-and-tell with me.

1581
01:22:43,567 --> 01:22:45,395
Ooh.When she gets
better, honey.

1582
01:22:50,052 --> 01:22:53,098
No, really, you guys,
she's going to be fine.

1583
01:22:53,142 --> 01:22:55,361
The fever's going to
break and she'll be fine.

1584
01:22:56,101 --> 01:22:57,233
Okay?

1585
01:22:59,496 --> 01:23:01,846
Well, it looks like you have
everything under control.

1586
01:23:11,290 --> 01:23:12,857
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

1587
01:23:14,467 --> 01:23:16,426
[BABY MONITOR
STATIC CRACKLING]

1588
01:23:30,483 --> 01:23:31,789
Hey, Mags.

1589
01:23:31,832 --> 01:23:33,182
How you doing?

1590
01:23:34,270 --> 01:23:35,836
Great horse, huh?

1591
01:23:41,059 --> 01:23:42,365
You know why we got it?

1592
01:23:43,931 --> 01:23:45,411
Well, I know you know.

1593
01:23:46,978 --> 01:23:48,371
I did pretty well, huh?

1594
01:23:50,112 --> 01:23:51,287
Move over.

1595
01:23:58,033 --> 01:24:01,514
You know all those times
I thought you were a pain?

1596
01:24:01,558 --> 01:24:03,908
Wearing your clothes, so
Mom would think you did.

1597
01:24:03,951 --> 01:24:05,170
Eating your food...

1598
01:24:05,214 --> 01:24:06,824
Fighting with you...

1599
01:24:06,867 --> 01:24:08,347
Doing your artwork...

1600
01:24:09,348 --> 01:24:10,784
Well, I was thinking,

1601
01:24:10,828 --> 01:24:12,438
if you had an
ordinary handicap,

1602
01:24:12,482 --> 01:24:14,919
like you were blind or deaf,

1603
01:24:14,962 --> 01:24:16,529
I'd be doing a lot of
stuff for you, right?

1604
01:24:19,141 --> 01:24:20,664
So, you're invisible.

1605
01:24:23,145 --> 01:24:25,799
I just want you to know,
you're not a pain.

1606
01:24:41,554 --> 01:24:43,121
[SIGHS]

1607
01:24:43,165 --> 01:24:44,340
Oh, Maggie.

1608
01:24:46,429 --> 01:24:48,735
You're getting sick a lot.

1609
01:24:48,779 --> 01:24:50,563
Something's changing,
I don't know.

1610
01:24:53,523 --> 01:24:56,047
TIM: [OVER BABY MONITOR] 
We have a wonderful family.

1611
01:24:56,091 --> 01:24:58,484
It's not like 
any other family,

1612
01:24:58,528 --> 01:25:01,661
and we may not make sense 
to other people, but...

1613
01:25:01,705 --> 01:25:04,186
It's our family
and it works, and...

1614
01:25:04,229 --> 01:25:05,404
You're a part of it.

1615
01:25:09,669 --> 01:25:11,193
I wish I could see you.

1616
01:25:14,326 --> 01:25:16,241
I wish I could hold you
the way Annie does.

1617
01:25:20,376 --> 01:25:23,553
But I can hold her,
and I can see her.

1618
01:25:24,858 --> 01:25:26,556
And maybe through her...

1619
01:25:27,470 --> 01:25:28,732
You feel it.

1620
01:25:31,517 --> 01:25:32,910
[SIGHS]

1621
01:25:32,953 --> 01:25:34,912
Yeah.

1622
01:25:34,955 --> 01:25:36,131
I'm a silly daddy.

1623
01:25:39,917 --> 01:25:41,658
[BABY MONITOR
STATIC CRACKLING]

1624
01:25:52,669 --> 01:25:54,410
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

1625
01:25:54,453 --> 01:25:56,194
TIM: Mmm.

1626
01:25:56,238 --> 01:25:57,848
Okay, kids.

1627
01:25:57,891 --> 01:25:59,980
Let's get a move on.
Time for school.

1628
01:26:00,024 --> 01:26:01,591
All right, you guys,
hop, hop.

1629
01:26:11,949 --> 01:26:12,950
[SOBBING]

1630
01:26:19,739 --> 01:26:21,219
DOC: Mom?

1631
01:26:21,263 --> 01:26:22,394
Dad?

1632
01:26:23,613 --> 01:26:25,571
[SNIFFLES]
Let me do this.

1633
01:26:36,365 --> 01:26:37,627
Kids...

1634
01:26:39,411 --> 01:26:40,847
[INHALING DEEPLY]

1635
01:26:40,891 --> 01:26:42,893
Your sister died last night...

1636
01:26:44,068 --> 01:26:46,157
In her sleep.

1637
01:26:46,201 --> 01:26:47,593
It was very peaceful.

1638
01:26:50,292 --> 01:26:52,250
Remember that angel that
you saw waiting in her room?

1639
01:26:54,078 --> 01:26:57,168
Well, it must have
been waiting for her.

1640
01:26:57,212 --> 01:26:59,518
And now Maggie's with God
and with all the angels.

1641
01:27:00,563 --> 01:27:02,782
Is Maggie a angel?

1642
01:27:02,826 --> 01:27:04,349
Mmm-hmm.

1643
01:27:04,393 --> 01:27:05,350
[ANNIE SNIFFLING]

1644
01:27:07,961 --> 01:27:09,006
Doc...

1645
01:27:11,182 --> 01:27:13,228
You know, too, that
Maggie's with the angels.

1646
01:27:14,359 --> 01:27:16,100
Yeah, Mom. I know.

1647
01:27:18,233 --> 01:27:19,538
Are you okay?

1648
01:27:21,061 --> 01:27:22,498
I'm sad.

1649
01:27:23,760 --> 01:27:25,240
For us and for me...

1650
01:27:26,328 --> 01:27:27,633
But not for Maggie.

1651
01:27:33,422 --> 01:27:35,250
SAM: Mom?What, honey?

1652
01:27:35,293 --> 01:27:36,729
Is Maggie with God?

1653
01:27:37,252 --> 01:27:39,471
Mmm-hmm.

1654
01:27:39,515 --> 01:27:42,431
One day Dad will be with God.

1655
01:27:42,474 --> 01:27:44,737
One day you'll be with God.

1656
01:27:44,781 --> 01:27:46,348
And Gilly...

1657
01:27:46,391 --> 01:27:49,002
And Doc, and me, too.

1658
01:27:49,046 --> 01:27:51,570
And then we'll all
come back, right?

1659
01:27:52,354 --> 01:27:54,181
I think so.

1660
01:27:54,225 --> 01:27:56,009
If God wants us to.

1661
01:27:56,053 --> 01:27:58,708
SAM: Mom, next time

1662
01:27:58,751 --> 01:28:01,624
I don't want Maggie
to be invisible, okay?

1663
01:28:03,103 --> 01:28:04,279
ANNIE: Okay.

1664
01:28:15,507 --> 01:28:17,117
[SNIFFLING]

1665
01:28:36,398 --> 01:28:39,575
Maggie...

1666
01:28:39,618 --> 01:28:42,317
I know your light
is shining brightly
wherever you are now.

1667
01:28:44,754 --> 01:28:46,669
But I know

1668
01:28:46,712 --> 01:28:48,235
you're still with us...

1669
01:28:50,586 --> 01:28:52,196
In our hearts, always.

1670
01:28:55,112 --> 01:28:57,636
Maggie, Sam asked me
to say this prayer.

1671
01:29:00,291 --> 01:29:02,641
ALL: Now I lay me
down to sleep

1672
01:29:02,685 --> 01:29:06,036
I pray the lord
my soul to keep

1673
01:29:06,079 --> 01:29:08,560
if I should die before I wake

1674
01:29:09,822 --> 01:29:11,171
I pray the lord

1675
01:29:11,215 --> 01:29:12,782
my soul to take.

1676
01:29:31,931 --> 01:29:33,411
Thank you.

1677
01:29:37,372 --> 01:29:38,764
[SOBBING]

